  <title>Floating-point numbers and Math</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>The last chapter focused on variables that were all integer values (<pf>int</pf> types). But often times we will want to work with values that are not integers; values like 3.14159 or 2.5. This chapter introduces how we can do so in C++ as well as the  of the math functions available to us in the <pf>cmath</pf> library to do more complex mathematics.</p>
